Rising Ibadan-based lightweight boxer, Samuel “Apata Roro” Moses, has called on boxing fans in the Oyo State capital to come out en masse and support him when he fights Wale Anifowose at GOtv Boxing Night 25 on 4 June. The bout is one of the seven scheduled for the event to be held at the Old Gymnasium of the Obafemi Awolowo Stadium. Speaking in a phone chat from his Ibadan base, Apata Roro said that he is happy to have the long-sought opportunity to fight at GOtv Boxing Night and vowed to make good use of it. -Advertisement- He added that he would require the fans’ support to put up a good showing that will see him defeat his opponent.